---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ratesData from '../data/rates.json';
---

<BaseLayout
  canonicalUrl="https://mortgagedash.app/terms/"
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service and Conditions for using MortgageDash."
>
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <div class="card p-8 sm:p-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8" style="color: var(--text-primary);">Terms of Service</h1>
      
      <div class="space-y-6" style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;">
        <p>Last updated: June 19, 2026</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>By accessing and using MortgageDash ("the Website"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you disagree with any part of the terms, you may not access the Website.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">2. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
        <p>All content, features, and functionality on this Website—including but not limited to the User Interface (UI), User Experience (UX) design, proprietary calculator logic, code, algorithms, text, graphics, and logos—are owned by MortgageDash and are protected by international copyright, trademark, patent, trade secret, and other intellectual property or proprietary rights laws.</p>
        <p>You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, create derivative works of, publicly display, publicly perform, republish, download, store, or transmit any of the material on our Website without our express written consent.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">3. Disclaimer of Accuracy & Static Data</h2>
        <p>The calculators and tools provided on MortgageDash are for educational and informational purposes only. By using this Website, you acknowledge and agree to the following regarding the accuracy of our data:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Principal & Interest (Exact):</strong> The core amortization math used to calculate your monthly Principal and Interest is exact and utilizes standard financial formulas.</li>
          <li><strong>Taxes, Insurance & PMI (Estimates):</strong> Any figures provided for Property Taxes, Homeowners Insurance, and Private Mortgage Insurance (PMI) are highly generalized <strong>estimates</strong> based on state-level averages. Your actual costs will vary significantly based on your specific county, city, property assessment, and personal credit score.</li>
          <li><strong>Static Data:</strong> Our state-level data (including median prices, tax rates, and insurance costs) is <strong>static</strong>. It is updated periodically but does <strong>not</strong> reflect real-time daily market fluctuations or live API feeds.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">We do not guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or usefulness of this information for your specific financial situation. The results provided by our calculators do not constitute a loan offer, binding agreement, or mortgage approval, and we cannot be held legally liable for any discrepancies between our estimates and your actual loan costs.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">4. Financial Advice Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>MortgageDash is not a lender, financial advisor, or broker. The content on this Website is not intended to be a substitute for professional financial advice. Always seek the advice of a qualified financial advisor or mortgage professional with any questions you may have regarding a mortgage or financial decision.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">5. Third-Party Brokers and Lenders</h2>
        <p>Any brokers, lenders, or third-party services listed on MortgageDash are provided solely for convenience and informational purposes. Their rankings or placements are based on third-party public review platforms (such as Trustpilot). We are not affiliated with these entities, and we do not guarantee or encourage the use of any specific broker or lender. By engaging with any third-party listed on our site, you acknowledge that you do so at your own risk and that MortgageDash holds no liability for their services, rates, or business practices.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>In no event shall MortgageDash, nor its directors, employees, partners, agents, suppliers, or affiliates, be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential or punitive damages, including without limitation, loss of profits, data, use, goodwill, or other intangible losses, resulting from your access to or use of or inability to access or use the Website.</p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4" style="color: var(--text-primary);">7. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms shall be governed and construed in accordance with the laws of the United States, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
